Measure the distance between the mounting holes on the back of the mounting bracket. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/58/Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/58/Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Mark the same distance on your chosen location. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/ed/Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/ed/Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Drill small holes at the marks. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/55/Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/55/Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Attach the mounting bracket to the surface with the screws. See "Tips" for seeking professional assistance. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/86/Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/86/Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Mount the rest of the detector into the bracket. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d8/Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d8/Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet5.jpg/v4-760px-Install-a-Smoke-Detector-or-Carbon-Monoxide-Detector-Step-4Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
